---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Cash Guy Nate"
  description="Privacy policy for Cash Guy Nate. How we collect, use, and protect your information."
  pageType="trust"
  crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Privacy Policy" }]}
>
  <section class="container container--narrow">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Effective date: January 1, {year}. Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}.</em></p>

    <p>
      {SITE.brandName} ("we," "us," "our") respects your privacy and is committed to handling your personal information responsibly. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share, and protect information when you interact with our website (azhomecashguy.com) or call our phone line.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Information you provide directly.</strong> When you call us or submit a contact form, we may collect your name, phone number, email address, property address, and the information you share about your property and situation.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> When you visit our website, we may collect technical information including IP address, browser type, device type, pages visited, referring URL, and time of visit. This data is collected via standard web logs and minimal analytics (Google Analytics 4 with IP anonymization).
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Phone call information.</strong> Inbound calls to our phone line may be recorded for quality and accuracy of offer documentation. By calling us, you consent to recording. If you do not consent, please state so at the start of the call.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use information</h2>
    <p>We use information you provide to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Evaluate properties and provide cash offers</li>
      <li>Schedule property visits and walk-throughs</li>
      <li>Communicate about pending transactions</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations (transaction records, IRS reporting, FinCEN requirements)</li>
      <li>Improve our service quality and our website</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we share information</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>We do not sell your information.</strong> We do not share lead data with other investors or marketing companies.
    </p>
    <p>We share information only with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Title companies, escrow agents, and attorneys involved in your specific transaction (with your knowledge)</li>
      <li>Service providers who help us operate the business (web hosting, accounting, legal counsel) under confidentiality obligations</li>
      <li>Government agencies when required by law (court orders, IRS, FinCEN, state tax authorities)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
    <p>
      Our website uses minimal cookies necessary for basic site functionality. We use Google Analytics 4 to understand traffic patterns; IP addresses are anonymized. We do not use marketing cookies, retargeting pixels, or cross-site tracking. You can disable cookies in your browser settings without affecting basic site functionality.
    </p>

    <h2>California residents (CCPA)</h2>
    <p>
      California residents have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Right to know what personal information we collect and how we use it</li>
      <li>Right to request deletion of personal information we hold about you</li>
      <li>Right to opt out of any sale of personal information (note: we do not sell personal information)</li>
      <li>Right to non-discrimination for exercising these rights</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise these rights, contact us at the phone number on this site or via the contact page. We will respond within 45 days as required by CCPA.
    </p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We retain contact and transaction information for as long as required by applicable law (typically 7 years for transaction records under IRS and AZ Department of Revenue rules). Non-transaction inquiry information is retained for 2 years and then deleted unless you request earlier deletion.
    </p>

    <h2>Data security</h2>
    <p>
      We use industry-standard security practices to protect personal information, including encrypted file storage, access controls on internal systems, and secure transmission (HTTPS) on our website. No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure; we do not guarantee absolute security.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Our services are not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If we learn we have collected such information, we will delete it promptly.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be posted with an updated "last updated" date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact us</h2>
    <p>
      For questions about this Privacy Policy or to exercise your privacy rights, call {SITE.phoneDisplay} or use the contact form on the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
